    <item>
      <title><![CDATA[Ministry Information]]></title>
      <link>http://www.oneplace.com/Ministries/Speak_up_with_Compassion</link>
      <description><![CDATA[

<p align=justify><B>Compassion International</B> is one of the world’s largest and fastest growing Christian child development organizations, working with more than 65 denominations and hundreds of indigenous church partners in Africa, Asia, Central and South America, and the Caribbean. Since 1952, Compassion has touched the lives of more than a million children. Learn more about this revolutionary approach to child development – visit <A href="http://www.compassion.com" target=_blank>www.compassion.com</A>   or call (800) 336-7676 and ask for the Compassion brochure entitled "God's Mandate."</p align=justify>]]></description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title><![CDATA[OurCompassion]]></title>
      <link>http://www.oneplace.com/Ministries/Speak_up_with_Compassion</link>
      <description><![CDATA[

<p align=justify> Today, Compassion serves over 800,000 supporters who are sponsoring more than one million children worldwide! Compassion believes there is huge potential for supporters to share, organize and speak up on behalf of children living in poverty. OurCompassion provides a venue for this social interaction so more children can be helped.</p align=justify><p align=justify>

OurCompassion is our new Web site to help you connect with other people sponsoring children in the same country or child development center as your child. Now that's joined together thinking.</p align=justify><p align=justify>

Read more about OurCompassion at the <a href="http://blog.compassion.com/joined-together-thinking/" target=blank<U>Compassion Blog</U></a>.</p align=justify>

<a href="http://www.ourcompassion.org/" target=blank<U>Visit OurCompassion.org today!</U></a>]]></description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title><![CDATA[One Million Changed Lives]]></title>
      <link>http://www.oneplace.com/Ministries/Speak_up_with_Compassion</link>
      <description><![CDATA[

<P align=justify>
Fellow Blewussi Kpodo is <I>Compassion's</I> 1 millionth sponsored child! <I>Compassion</I> has helped over 2 million children over their 57-year history, but 8-year-old Fellow marks a moment in the ministry's history where <I>1 million children are being helped all at one time!</I> </P align=justify><P align=justify>
Fellow's sponsor is Jang Mi-Ran, a long-time <I>Compassion</I> supporter and Olympic gold medalist weight lifter from Korea.
</P align=justify><P align=justify>
So, the strongest woman in the world is now sponsoring one of the most vulnerable children in the world!
</P align=justify><P align=justify>


Read more about Fellow at the <a href="http://www.responsetrack.net/lnk/compassion/1936222/?151X50001C4http://blog.compassion.com/tag/one-millionth-child/"target=_Blank<U>Compassion Blog</U></a>. 
</P align=justify>

]]></description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title><![CDATA[Too Small to Ignore]]></title>
      <link>http://www.oneplace.com/Ministries/Speak_up_with_Compassion</link>
      <description><![CDATA[
Now in paperback with Study Guide!
<p align=justify>The award-winning book, <i>Too Small to Ignore: Why The Least of These Matters Most</i> is the powerful story of Wess Stafford's boyhood adventures in Africa, his dramatic calling to minister to children, and why we as Christians are called to speak up for children. </p><p align=justify>
Using inspiring true stories from his childhood in a small African village and many years of child development experience as President of Compassion International, Dr. Stafford paints a vivid picture of how the world's children are so often ignored in today's society...and how that is so far from what God intended. </p><p align=justify>
This moving manifesto unveils God's heart for children and the poor, while offering real-world suggestions and resources to help us fulfill the calling to reach out to "the least of these." 
View this moving <a href="http://www.toosmalltoignore.com/" target=_blank>video montage</a> of Wess sharing his heart and his life's mission.</p align=justify>]]></description>
